&lt;p&gt;This is a&lt;strong&gt; hybrid &lt;/strong&gt;position based out of our &lt;strong&gt;Palo Alto, New York, or Washington, D.C.&lt;/strong&gt; offices. Reporting directly to the Executive Leadership Team, you will be expected to work onsite 2–3 days per week based on business needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Administration: &lt;/strong&gt;Independently execute a high volume of complex administrative tasks in a timely manner with flawless attention to detail, including proactive calendar management, end-to-end travel logistics, and meticulous expense management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Special Projects: &lt;/strong&gt;Lead and manage special projects from conception to completion as assigned by the executive.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meeting Governance:&lt;/strong&gt; Coordinate executive meetings by owning agenda preparation, material distribution, and logistics. Drive post-meeting momentum by tracking action items, summarizing key decisions, and ensuring accountability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Global Offsites: &lt;/strong&gt;End-to-end planning, budgeting, and execution of high-impact executive team offsites across multiple global regions (requires occasional travel).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Excellence: &lt;/strong&gt;Model efficient daily operations, proactively identifying process bottlenecks and introducing new process strategies to improve team velocity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration: &lt;/strong&gt;Partner closely with the broader A/EBP cohort to ensure seamless execution of recurring domestic and international meetings, events, and strategic projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Onboarding Support: &lt;/strong&gt;Anchor and optimize the onboarding experience for new leadership reporting to your executive.&lt;/li&gt;
