&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Wing:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Wing offers drone delivery as a safe, fast, and sustainable solution for last mile logistics. Consumer appetites for on-demand services are increasing, but current delivery methods are inefficient, costly, and contribute to road accidents and air pollution. Wing’s fleet of highly automated delivery drones can transport small packages directly from businesses to homes on-demand, in minutes. We design, build, and operate our aircraft, and offer drone delivery services on two continents. Our technology is designed to be easy to integrate into existing delivery and logistics networks, offering a scalable drone delivery solution for a broad range of businesses. Wing is a part of Google&#39;s parent company, Alphabet, and our mission is to create the preferred means of delivery for the planet. If you&#39;re ready to do the greatest work of your life, come join us.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wing is looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Analytics Manager&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;to join our &lt;strong&gt;Analytics&lt;/strong&gt; team. This role is based in &lt;strong&gt;Palo Alto, CA or remotely in the US.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is solution-oriented, a self-starter, and thrives in ambiguity, using data and analytics to turn complex business questions into clear, decision-focused problems. They analyze complex datasets, design and build robust models, and conduct scenario analyses to evaluate tradeoffs, quantify impact, and guide strategic choices. They communicate insights through actionable recommendations, enabling leadership to make confident, data-informed decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze complex datasets to uncover trends, patterns, and insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify the right data sources to answer ambiguous business questions and ensure analyses are accurate and actionable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and build robust models to evaluate tradeoffs and quantify impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct scenario analyses and sensitivity testing to support strategic decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Synthesize analytical findings into clear, executive-level recommendations for senior leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategize, develop, and scale dashboards, automated workflows, and self-serve analytics to operationalize insights across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with leadership to frame ambiguous problems into well-defined analytical questions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Need:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years in analytics, data science, business analytics, consulting, or strategic data roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s/Master’s degree in a quantitative field (e.g. data analytics, math).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong experience in data analysis, modeling, and applied analytics (SQL, Excel, Python, or similar tools).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to work with ambiguous, complex business problems and turn them into actionable solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and storytelling skills, with the ability to present complex analyses in a clear, decision-focused way.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building scenario models, forecasts, or tradeoff analyses to guide business decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated leadership and ownership mindset with the ability to manage end-to-end project lifecycles, prioritize high-impact workstreams, and deliver measurable results across cross-functional teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to influence decisions and partner with leadership across multiple functions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Wing:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Wing offers drone delivery as a safe, fast, and sustainable solution for last mile logistics. Consumer appetites for on-demand services are increasing, but current delivery methods are inefficient, costly, and contribute to road accidents and air pollution. Wing’s fleet of highly automated delivery drones can transport small packages directly from businesses to homes on-demand, in minutes. We design, build, and operate our aircraft, and offer drone delivery services on two continents. Our technology is designed to be easy to integrate into existing delivery and logistics networks, offering a scalable drone delivery solution for a broad range of businesses. Wing is a part of Google&#39;s parent company, Alphabet, and our mission is to create the preferred means of delivery for the planet. If you&#39;re ready to do the greatest work of your life, come join us.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wing is looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Aviation Safety Analyst&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;to join our &lt;strong&gt;Aviation Safety&lt;/strong&gt; team. This role will be &lt;strong&gt;hybrid&lt;/strong&gt; based in &lt;strong&gt;Palo Alto, California&lt;/strong&gt;. As an Aviation Safety Analyst, you will play a critical role in supporting the Safety Management System (SMS) by assisting teams in fulfilling SMS requirements and ensuring compliance with Safety policies and procedures. You will balance your time between conducting formal Safety Risk Management (SRM) activities and executing Safety Assurance functions, specifically through data analytics, safety performance monitoring, and safety investigations. You will act as a bridge between raw operational data and actionable insights, ensuring responsible parties have the comprehensive information they need to keep our operations safe and efficient.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze safety data sets to identify trends and emerging risks, including building and maintaining safety performance charts and dashboards to visualize the effectiveness of our operational controls&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams to conduct risk assessments on new technologies, operational concepts, and proposed flight environments to identify hazards and develop robust controls&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct thorough safety investigations into reports or events, utilizing root-cause analysis to ensure we learn from every event and implement effective corrective actions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform safety reviews on proposed organizational or operational changes to ensure that existing safety levels are maintained and no new hazards are introduced&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner daily with Engineering, Flight Operations, and Flight Test teams to ensure safety data is accurate and that risk assessments reflect the reality of our operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support safety promotion activities by assisting with safety training sessions and crafting communications to share safety-critical information and lessons learned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Need:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of experience in a regulated safety environment, preferably in aviation or autonomous systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience in safety data analysis, both quantitative and qualitative, with the ability to &quot;tell the story&quot; behind the numbers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A thorough understanding of all SMS components and how they interact to create a proactive safety environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to facilitate risk assessments and document hazards and mitigations clear

