&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This role will report into VP of Hardware Development &amp;amp; Manufacturing Operations and partner across Engineering and Business Operations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute Wing’s manufacturing strategy to align production capabilities with business goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage Product Operations, Operations Program Management, Process Engineering, Quality, Forward Logistics, Reverse Logistics and Manufacturing Partner Management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Engineering teams to build product roadmaps and execute plans from Concept and NPI through production and EOL.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive operational excellence to minimize waste, optimize workflows, improve quality and enhance overall productivity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the manufacturing operations budget to adhere to financial targets and resource allocations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and maintain rigorous quality assurance protocols to ensure all products meet industry standards and regulatory requirements for reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enforce compliance standards across all facilities, leading audits and training programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the supply chain and logistics teams to manage inventory levels, optimize vendor relations, and ensure timely delivery of products to meet business needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the implementation of advanced manufacturing technologies and automated systems to improve production capacity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
