&lt;p&gt;Wing is looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Field HR Manager &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;to join our &lt;strong&gt;People&lt;/strong&gt; team. This role is &lt;strong&gt;hybrid&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;based in &lt;strong&gt;Dallas, Texas&lt;/strong&gt;. The ideal candidate has a passion for employee relations, collaborating with field staff, process improvement and operational excellence. They will understand industry best practices and be excited about working with dynamic clients in a cutting-edge industry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will help solve complex organizational challenges using people-related solutions to ultimately push our mission and business goals forward:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver &lt;strong&gt;HR consultation&lt;/strong&gt; to managers and their teams on a variety of HR topics including resolution of employee questions on company policies, benefits, and compensation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the expert in handling &lt;strong&gt;employee relations issues in the field&lt;/strong&gt;, and ensure adherence to our Code of Conduct, Employee Handbook and cultural / behavioral expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
